edu.umd.cs.psl.model.atom

Class AtomCache

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.umd.cs.psl.model.atom.AtomCache

  • public class AtomCache
extends java.lang.Object
    Storage for GroundAtoms so that a Database always returns the same object for a GroundAtom.

    Also serves as the factory for GroundAtoms for a Database.

      • instantiateObservedAtom

        public ObservedAtom instantiateObservedAtom(Predicate p,
                                   GroundTerm[] args,
                                   double value,
                                   double confidence)
        Instantiates an ObservedAtom and stores it in this AtomCache.

        This method should only be called by this AtomCache's Database. To retrieve a GroundAtom, all others should use Database.getAtom(Predicate, GroundTerm[]) or AtomManager.getAtom(Predicate, GroundTerm[]).

        Further, this method should only be called after ensuring that the Atom is not already in this AtomCache using getCachedAtom(QueryAtom).

        Parameters:
        p - the Predicate of the Atom
        args - the arguments to this Atom
        value - the Atom's truth value
        confidence - the Atom's confidence value
        Returns:
        the new ObservedAtom
